commit.message:
Added config modules to the shiro-all .jar

git-svn-id: https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/shiro/trunk@1484197 13f79535-47bb-0310-9956-ffa450edef68

Moved configuration-related code to a new module.  This decouples configuration issues from Shiro's core API since config is largely environment specific (Ini, Tapestry, Spring, Guice, etc).  This also (finally) removes shiro-core's dependency on Apache Commons BeanUtils.

BeanUtils is now only a dependency if you're using Shiro's OGDL (Object Graph Definition Language-style configuration, like ini config.

Finally, some shared/common utility code was moved to shiro-lang.

git-svn-id: https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/shiro/trunk@1484196 13f79535-47bb-0310-9956-ffa450edef68

Updated aggregate (uber) jar with the project's updated dependency list.  

I *think* this will also resolve transitive dependencies in a maven build (but I have to test this).  I suspect the uber jar will be more desirable - as long as transitive dependencies can be resolved - now that we're splitting Shiro into more targeted .jars.
